Risk appetite describes the amount and the type of risks which the firm is willing to take;
Risk capacity describes the maximum amount of risk which a firm can absorb;
FRB(Federal Reserve Board) conduct 2 stress testing exercises:

Dot-Frank Act Stress Test for asset size larger than USD 10 billion;
Comprehensive Capital Analysis and Review for asset size larger than USD 50 billion;

Most institutions set two types of limits:

Tier 1, risk that is specified, an overall limit by asset class;
Tier 2, more generalized risk related areas of business activities;

